defs:
1.to wait
; 2. (intransitive, or transitive with por or with no preposition) to wait (for); to await; 3. (transitive, auxiliary with a verb in the personal infinitive as the second object) to wait for (not to do anything until); 4.to hope
; 5. (transitive with por) to hope for (to really want something); 6. (ditransitive, with the indirect object taking que and a verb in the present subjunctive) to hope (that) someone does something; 7. (auxiliary with a verb in the personal or impersonal infinitive) to hope something can be done; 8. (intransitive, or transitive with por or with no preposition) to expect; to anticipate (to know or think that something will happen);
